1
00:00:00,340 --> 00:00:01,340
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,410 --> 00:00:02,410
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:02,470 --> 00:00:05,280
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:25,260 --> 00:00:26,600
(Episode 36)

5
00:00:26,970 --> 00:00:28,300
Hyun Jun, you...

6
00:00:29,230 --> 00:00:30,600
Since everyone's here,

7
00:00:31,640 --> 00:00:32,870
I have some good news to share.

8
00:00:37,080 --> 00:00:38,080
Chloe and I...

9
00:00:42,110 --> 00:00:43,110
are getting married.

10
00:00:45,150 --> 00:00:46,320
Park Hyun Jun!

11
00:00:47,390 --> 00:00:49,050
What in the world?

12
00:01:13,910 --> 00:01:15,750
Ms. Choi is here.

13
00:01:22,020 --> 00:01:23,120
Is something up?

14
00:01:23,460 --> 00:01:25,020
Ms. Choi, what brings you here?

15
00:01:27,230 --> 00:01:28,960
The chairman sent for you.

16
00:01:33,670 --> 00:01:35,730
He summoned her urgently
at this hour?

17
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:39,640
Even without help
from President Kim,

18
00:01:40,340 --> 00:01:43,170
he's suspicious of Choi Yu Na.

19
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:47,550
Surely she's not using
the wedding as a cover...

20
00:01:47,610 --> 00:01:50,050
to come here and frame Ms. Choi.

21
00:01:50,650 --> 00:01:51,880
She wouldn't go that far.

22
00:01:53,590 --> 00:01:55,590
Chloe, you should leave.

23
00:01:56,520 --> 00:02:00,390
Showing up unannounced
to say you're marrying my son...

24
00:02:01,090 --> 00:02:02,090
is just disrespectful.

25
00:02:02,590 --> 00:02:03,730
It was my idea.

26
00:02:04,300 --> 00:02:05,800
Please give us your blessing.

27
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:07,100
Zip it.

28
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:08,600
Who said you could marry her?

29
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:12,040
I'll take care of this,

30
00:02:12,540 --> 00:02:13,970
so please don't worry.

31
00:02:14,670 --> 00:02:17,280
Ms. Choi, my study. Now.

32
00:02:18,040 --> 00:02:19,040
Father!

33
00:02:21,510 --> 00:02:23,950
If you need the chairman's approval,
let me know.

34
00:02:24,980 --> 00:02:27,220
I can at least help you two
get married.

35
00:02:27,920 --> 00:02:29,050
Worry about yourself.

36
00:02:31,090 --> 00:02:32,890
He's right about that.

37
00:02:33,460 --> 00:02:36,030
You should be more worried
about yourself, Ms. Choi.

38
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:38,060
What's that supposed to mean?

39
00:02:38,660 --> 00:02:40,930
If you're that curious,
go in and see for yourself.

40
00:02:51,440 --> 00:02:52,610
You. Get over here.

41
00:02:57,350 --> 00:02:59,620
Maybe we should talk some more.

42
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:14,430
How dare you...

43
00:03:15,870 --> 00:03:17,400
rummage through my study?

44
00:03:18,740 --> 00:03:19,740
That's...

45
00:03:23,140 --> 00:03:25,240
That's what you get
for not taking me seriously.

46
00:03:25,810 --> 00:03:28,450
You made a promise,
so you should've helped...

47
00:03:28,450 --> 00:03:30,080
move up my wedding.

48
00:03:30,620 --> 00:03:33,020
Instead of spending your time
on exclusive development deals...

49
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:35,890
You had the nerve
to read my documents?

50
00:03:36,790 --> 00:03:40,220
Now you're even
going through my things!

51
00:03:40,790 --> 00:03:41,790
Why, you...

52
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:45,660
I have proof.

53
00:03:45,660 --> 00:03:47,930
What? Proof?

54
00:03:48,330 --> 00:03:49,330
Right here.

55
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,340
I took pictures of everything.

56
00:03:53,070 --> 00:03:55,070
If I go to the police
with these photos,

57
00:03:55,640 --> 00:03:57,210
do you think
you can handle the fallout?

58
00:03:57,210 --> 00:03:58,740
You'll go to the police...

59
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:00,210
with that as evidence?

60
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:04,280
The police? Why, you...

61
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:12,320
- Give it to me!
- No!

62
00:04:14,930 --> 00:04:17,930
Did you seriously think I'd fall...

63
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:19,830
for your tricks again?

64
00:04:20,030 --> 00:04:21,470
That's not all I've got.

65
00:04:22,930 --> 00:04:24,940
I still have an audio recording.

66
00:04:24,940 --> 00:04:26,300
Of course.

67
00:04:27,310 --> 00:04:30,140
You still have that.

68
00:04:31,340 --> 00:04:35,180
That's the only reason
you're still alive.

69
00:04:36,510 --> 00:04:38,880
I don't want to use
the recording against you,

70
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:43,290
so take care of my wedding
right now.

71
00:04:43,450 --> 00:04:45,790
Keep the promise you made
seven years ago!

72
00:04:49,630 --> 00:04:52,200
You told me to take
everything Baek Jin Ju has...

73
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:53,600
and make it mine.

74
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:57,900
And the one thing she had
that I wanted most...

75
00:04:58,540 --> 00:04:59,870
was Min Jun.

76
00:05:00,870 --> 00:05:03,680
It's the compensation
I've rightfully earned!

77
00:05:06,380 --> 00:05:09,050
You stabbed me in the back,
and now you want to marry my son?

78
00:05:09,150 --> 00:05:10,420
A marriage?

79
00:05:15,390 --> 00:05:16,620
A marriage, is it?

80
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:25,500
You'll marry her?

81
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:28,500
I said no to marrying that vixen.

82
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:30,100
Ms. Oh.

83
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:33,910
Mom, could you give up on Father?

84
00:05:34,570 --> 00:05:35,570
What?

85
00:05:35,670 --> 00:05:37,980
Could you let
someone else have Adele?

86
00:05:38,110 --> 00:05:39,680
How can you compare Adele
to that witch?

87
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:41,950
To me, they're the same.

88
00:05:42,310 --> 00:05:44,380
I can never give her up,
and losing her is...

89
00:05:46,650 --> 00:05:48,320
more than I can bear.

90
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:50,350
What if she leaves you?

91
00:05:50,460 --> 00:05:51,460
Mom!

92
00:05:51,460 --> 00:05:52,890
If you keep insisting,

93
00:05:53,690 --> 00:05:56,730
I'll make Chloe, that witch,
change her mind.

94
00:05:57,360 --> 00:05:58,660
If I choose to,

95
00:05:58,660 --> 00:06:00,530
bringing someone down
is nothing to me.

96
00:06:00,900 --> 00:06:04,270
Do you think Chloe is the one
you'll end up crushing?

97
00:06:07,140 --> 00:06:08,670
If you do anything to Chloe,

98
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:11,240
I won't fight you.

99
00:06:11,540 --> 00:06:14,410
I'll keep falling apart
in front of you...

100
00:06:14,410 --> 00:06:15,880
until there's nothing left of me.

101
00:06:17,750 --> 00:06:21,190
How dare you threaten your mother
like that?

102
00:06:24,890 --> 00:06:26,090
Because I love her.

103
00:06:29,660 --> 00:06:32,060
More deeply than you can imagine.

104
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,940
I'm actually in love.

105
00:06:45,910 --> 00:06:48,210
What game are you playing?

106
00:06:48,750 --> 00:06:51,020
Since when were you and Hyun Jun...

107
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:53,480
I don't see why I should
explain myself to you...

108
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,920
when you're not even his mother.

109
00:06:57,920 --> 00:06:59,460
Fine, I'll ask something else.

110
00:06:59,860 --> 00:07:00,890
The chairman...

111
00:07:01,960 --> 00:07:06,300
believes Ms. Choi reported
the fake appraisal to the police.

112
00:07:07,870 --> 00:07:09,870
Did you frame her ahead of time?

113
00:07:10,670 --> 00:07:12,100
Is that why you rushed over here,

114
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:14,770
to ask for his blessing
on your marriage?

115
00:07:15,010 --> 00:07:19,680
Was it all to frame Ms. Choi before
I had the chance to say anything?

116
00:07:21,510 --> 00:07:23,010
Think whatever you want.

117
00:07:23,580 --> 00:07:25,120
This is as far as you will go.

118
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:30,720
You used your wedding as a cover
to frame Ms. Choi...

119
00:07:30,890 --> 00:07:32,760
and involved yourself
in this fake appraisal case.

120
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:36,160
I want you to stay out of it.

121
00:07:36,630 --> 00:07:38,400
I was about to say the same thing.

122
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:43,070
Whether I marry or frame someone,
just stay out of my business.

123
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:47,840
That's the only way
I can keep your secret, after all.

124
00:08:12,330 --> 00:08:16,070
As you can probably tell,
no one is happy about this marriage.

125
00:08:16,930 --> 00:08:19,340
Marriage isn't
all about celebration.

126
00:08:22,370 --> 00:08:26,180
I want you to have a marriage
that everyone can celebrate.

127
00:08:27,450 --> 00:08:30,750
I want your marriage to be so happy
there's no room for me in it.

128
00:08:31,150 --> 00:08:34,950
But a rushed marriage like this,
without any real love or happiness?

129
00:08:37,790 --> 00:08:40,020
It isn't fair to you.

130
00:08:48,230 --> 00:08:49,770
You're still here?

131
00:08:49,770 --> 00:08:52,140
I was just on my way out.

132
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:55,370
Actually, since it has come to this,

133
00:08:56,140 --> 00:08:58,040
let's settle this marriage issue.

134
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:00,750
- Mrs. Ok!
- Yes, sir.

135
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:03,850
Have everyone gather here.

136
00:09:04,350 --> 00:09:05,380
Yes, sir.

137
00:09:16,390 --> 00:09:18,960
This is a family matter.
Please stay out of it.

138
00:09:20,830 --> 00:09:22,530
But we live in this house too.

139
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:28,110
Aren't you even a little curious
what's going on, Mrs. Ok?

140
00:09:28,810 --> 00:09:32,780
Two wives, two sons,
and two potential daughters-in-law.

141
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:36,610
The chairman will just do
what he always does.

142
00:09:37,010 --> 00:09:39,520
And what is it he always does?

143
00:09:46,420 --> 00:09:49,430
I've decided to settle
this marriage issue.

144
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:51,160
Marriage?

145
00:09:51,830 --> 00:09:52,930
Whose marriage?

146
00:09:53,130 --> 00:09:57,230
Ms. Choi and Chloe both want
to marry into the family,

147
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:01,270
but neither of them
meets my standards.

148
00:10:02,970 --> 00:10:04,780
That's why I'll only accept...

149
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:08,280
the person who proves more capable.

150
00:10:11,020 --> 00:10:12,050
Only one?

151
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:15,150
You're putting Ms. Choi
and Chloe to the test?

152
00:10:15,690 --> 00:10:19,120
Are you running that
"who's better" competition again?

153
00:10:20,060 --> 00:10:21,060
What's next?

154
00:10:21,060 --> 00:10:24,500
Why not have a competition
to see who croaks first?

155
00:10:26,830 --> 00:10:30,430
Seriously, why turn everything
into a competition, even marriage?

156
00:10:30,770 --> 00:10:34,210
Just say no to Hyun Jun's marriage
and be done with it.

157
00:10:35,070 --> 00:10:36,140
I won't give up.

158
00:10:38,310 --> 00:10:39,540
I can't agree to this.

159
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:42,450
My marriage was promised long ago.

160
00:10:42,510 --> 00:10:44,750
The man you want to marry
is clearly against it,

161
00:10:45,220 --> 00:10:48,150
but the other couple is ready
to get married.

162
00:10:49,020 --> 00:10:50,020
What's wrong?

163
00:10:50,290 --> 00:10:53,690
Afraid you can't beat Chloe
in a competition?

164
00:10:54,230 --> 00:10:56,830
Sir, if you do this...

165
00:10:57,830 --> 00:10:58,900
What if I do?

166
00:10:59,300 --> 00:11:01,700
So you want to fight me now?
Is that it?

167
00:11:05,770 --> 00:11:08,310
I'll do as you wish, sir.

168
00:11:14,410 --> 00:11:17,480
Do as he wishes?
Forget the test or whatever.

169
00:11:17,550 --> 00:11:19,220
Stay away from my son, you witch.

170
00:11:19,220 --> 00:11:21,490
I told you not
to treat Chloe like that.

171
00:11:23,490 --> 00:11:25,260
Everyone, quiet!

172
00:11:29,830 --> 00:11:32,830
Either compete
or give up on marrying my son.

173
00:11:34,030 --> 00:11:37,200
Anyone who objects can leave
my house right now!

174
00:11:51,380 --> 00:11:53,780
I have no intention of taking part
in this competition.

175
00:11:55,350 --> 00:11:58,820
Regardless of the outcome,
I will not be marrying Choi Yu Na.

176
00:12:01,590 --> 00:12:03,530
If you want me to leave, I will.

177
00:12:04,030 --> 00:12:05,260
Just say the word.

178
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:07,200
Min Jun.

179
00:12:13,970 --> 00:12:16,170
Well, him...

180
00:12:16,470 --> 00:12:19,240
I'll leave it to you
to get him in line.

181
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:34,960
So,

182
00:12:35,590 --> 00:12:37,160
how are you going to test them?

183
00:12:38,130 --> 00:12:39,400
Soon enough,

184
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:42,300
I'll give you
a comprehensive assignment.

185
00:12:42,970 --> 00:12:44,070
Be ready.

186
00:12:47,570 --> 00:12:50,140
And let me make one thing
perfectly clear.

187
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:53,180
Whoever loses the competition...

188
00:12:54,350 --> 00:12:58,780
will have to give up the wedding
and be fired from the company.

189
00:12:59,880 --> 00:13:00,950
You'll fire us too?

190
00:13:01,920 --> 00:13:04,960
Why risk things
being awkward at work...

191
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:06,860
once you call off the wedding?

192
00:13:07,930 --> 00:13:09,560
If you realize
you're not meant to be,

193
00:13:10,290 --> 00:13:12,930
you should make a clean break.

194
00:13:31,450 --> 00:13:33,320
Come up with an appropriate task.

195
00:13:33,820 --> 00:13:37,050
Ms. Choi is no match for Chloe.

196
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:40,290
When Ms. Choi's cornered
and her lack of skill is exposed,

197
00:13:42,730 --> 00:13:46,730
she'll be forced to bring me
that audio recording herself.

198
00:13:47,900 --> 00:13:49,070
Set it up that way.

199
00:13:49,770 --> 00:13:51,400
Yes, sir. Understood.

200
00:13:56,940 --> 00:13:59,410
Once I get that recording back,

201
00:14:00,410 --> 00:14:03,650
she'll pay the price
for daring to backstab me...

202
00:14:04,580 --> 00:14:06,650
with her life.

203
00:14:07,850 --> 00:14:09,790
She reported the fake appraisal
to the police...

204
00:14:10,350 --> 00:14:13,290
and tried to use
my lobbying documents against me.

205
00:14:15,230 --> 00:14:16,890
I can't let someone like that live.

206
00:14:31,380 --> 00:14:34,610
(Park Tae Ho)

207
00:14:35,210 --> 00:14:36,910
A competition to decide
who gets married?

208
00:14:37,620 --> 00:14:40,720
No, He's using this competition...

209
00:14:40,780 --> 00:14:42,650
to get rid of Choi Yu Na.

210
00:14:43,250 --> 00:14:44,760
If I play this right,

211
00:14:45,460 --> 00:14:48,930
I can make Choi Yu Na
despise Park Tae Ho.

212
00:14:50,590 --> 00:14:51,600
Chloe!

213
00:14:56,670 --> 00:14:58,370
What do you think you're doing?

214
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,270
"I'll do as you wish, sir."

215
00:15:02,070 --> 00:15:05,010
You said you'd help me get married,
so why are you butting in?

216
00:15:05,480 --> 00:15:10,010
Of course, it would be a problem
if you were eliminated too easily.

217
00:15:10,850 --> 00:15:12,780
You need to hang on until the end...

218
00:15:13,250 --> 00:15:15,420
so you can take down
Park Tae Ho for me.

219
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:19,220
You don't need to worry.

220
00:15:19,890 --> 00:15:22,430
Our deal is still on.

221
00:15:22,890 --> 00:15:27,300
I'll pretend to compete,
but I'll actually help you win.

222
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:29,270
And why should I believe you?

223
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:32,870
If you start to doubt me,
go ahead and tell the chairman.

224
00:15:33,340 --> 00:15:36,070
Tell him I'm only marrying
into the family...

225
00:15:36,070 --> 00:15:37,840
to get control of the bio division.

226
00:15:40,610 --> 00:15:43,550
You'd better mean what you say.

227
00:15:44,010 --> 00:15:45,850
If you try to pull something,

228
00:15:45,850 --> 00:15:47,550
I'll go straight to him,
as you said.

229
00:16:03,230 --> 00:16:04,770
Do you have a minute to talk?

230
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:07,040
Sure. Come on in.

231
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:22,120
You just got back
from the police station,

232
00:16:22,550 --> 00:16:23,790
and now this?

233
00:16:25,090 --> 00:16:27,260
- Are you okay?
- What about you?

234
00:16:27,590 --> 00:16:28,760
Are you good?

235
00:16:30,290 --> 00:16:33,900
Aren't you bothered
by their wedding announcement?

236
00:16:36,370 --> 00:16:38,470
Do you want Chloe to win?

237
00:16:41,910 --> 00:16:45,540
Part of me wants her to win
because it's what she wants.

238
00:16:46,540 --> 00:16:48,510
But because I want her for myself,

239
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:51,080
I also find myself wishing
she would lose.

240
00:16:53,620 --> 00:16:57,020
Chloe and Baek Jin Ju are
two completely different people.

241
00:16:58,120 --> 00:17:02,330
I had Mrs. Han at Ihwachae
look into it thoroughly.

242
00:17:03,560 --> 00:17:06,260
My feelings for Chloe
and for Jin Ju...

243
00:17:06,700 --> 00:17:07,770
are two different things.

244
00:17:07,770 --> 00:17:08,830
So you're saying...

245
00:17:10,700 --> 00:17:13,700
you've genuinely developed feelings
for Chloe?

246
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:15,640
Yes.

247
00:17:21,180 --> 00:17:22,780
You need to let those feelings go.

248
00:17:24,110 --> 00:17:27,020
Chloe might be
a valuable business partner,

249
00:17:27,120 --> 00:17:28,920
but she's not right for you.

250
00:17:29,050 --> 00:17:31,360
I wouldn't have approved.

251
00:17:33,790 --> 00:17:35,960
You sound just like you did
seven years ago.

252
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:43,000
You said studying abroad with Jin Ju
was impossible and forbade it.

253
00:17:43,100 --> 00:17:44,270
Because of you,

254
00:17:45,440 --> 00:17:48,640
I spent seven years of my life
full of regret and resentment.

255
00:17:50,510 --> 00:17:51,580
This time,

256
00:17:52,080 --> 00:17:54,850
I'm not going to make
the same mistake.

257
00:18:14,930 --> 00:18:17,370
It's late, Manager Kang.
What is this about?

258
00:18:18,340 --> 00:18:21,870
There's an urgent matter
I must report to the chairman.

259
00:18:22,010 --> 00:18:23,010
Excuse me.

260
00:18:34,150 --> 00:18:38,420
(Adele)

261
00:18:38,960 --> 00:18:41,760
That bag yesterday
must have been full of money.

262
00:18:42,490 --> 00:18:44,030
He must've sent it...

263
00:18:44,030 --> 00:18:46,930
to appease Assemblyman Kwon
after my arrest.

264
00:18:47,970 --> 00:18:49,400
If he returned it,

265
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:51,370
does that mean
the exclusive development deal...

266
00:18:51,370 --> 00:18:52,540
is off the table?

267
00:18:52,970 --> 00:18:55,670
Chairman Park isn't one
to give up easily.

268
00:18:56,170 --> 00:18:59,480
Ultimately, Assemblyman Kwon
is the one holding all the cards.

269
00:19:02,210 --> 00:19:06,550
(BIT Life, President Kim Myung Hui)

270
00:19:08,190 --> 00:19:10,090
He's a man
who cares about his reputation.

271
00:19:11,260 --> 00:19:13,260
But he's also very greedy.

272
00:19:14,630 --> 00:19:18,700
If reputation matters more,
a scandal would make him fold.

273
00:19:19,430 --> 00:19:23,070
And he'd drop the deal
with Chairman Park entirely.

274
00:19:23,930 --> 00:19:24,970
But...

275
00:19:25,870 --> 00:19:27,970
if his greed is stronger,

276
00:19:29,940 --> 00:19:31,380
then we can't let our guard down.

277
00:19:32,940 --> 00:19:35,910
(BIT Life, President Kim Myung Hui)

278
00:19:38,820 --> 00:19:41,150
Kim Myung Hui, get out here now!

279
00:19:43,390 --> 00:19:45,290
- Just a moment!
- Then what are we supposed to do?

280
00:19:47,860 --> 00:19:49,830
There's no need to cause a scene.

281
00:19:50,460 --> 00:19:53,330
If you don't trust the report,
go to the AD Appraisal Institute...

282
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:55,300
and get a second opinion.

283
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:59,400
She said the ornament wasn't fake,
just misappraised.

284
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:02,710
How can we trust an institute
that was run by an appraiser...

285
00:20:02,710 --> 00:20:04,470
who made a mistake like that?

286
00:20:04,640 --> 00:20:07,610
Fine, we'll get another appraisal
somewhere else,

287
00:20:07,740 --> 00:20:09,850
so give us our money back.

288
00:20:10,550 --> 00:20:12,780
- Tell Kim Myung Hui to come here!
- Get her down here!

289
00:20:13,420 --> 00:20:15,550
- Please don't do this.
- What will you do about this?

290
00:20:15,550 --> 00:20:17,490
Someone has to take care of this!

291
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:21,560
That's enough.

292
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:26,300
- Hey, it's Kim Myung Hui!
- It's her. It's Kim Myung Hui!

293
00:20:26,660 --> 00:20:29,770
- It's Kim Myung Hui!
- What about these appraisals?

294
00:20:29,770 --> 00:20:31,270
Everyone, please step back.

295
00:20:31,870 --> 00:20:33,870
You need to take
responsibility for this!

296
00:20:33,940 --> 00:20:36,310
- You must be held accountable!
- This is how you do business?

297
00:20:36,370 --> 00:20:37,440
(AD Appraisals:
Gemstone Appraisal Report)

298
00:20:37,510 --> 00:20:39,910
You call this an appraisal?
Is that what this is?

299
00:20:41,510 --> 00:20:43,580
These appraisals weren't cheap,
you know.

300
00:20:44,080 --> 00:20:46,680
Regardless of the reason,
the mistake was mine,

301
00:20:46,750 --> 00:20:48,620
and I apologize for the concern
I have caused.

302
00:20:49,550 --> 00:20:51,250
Forget your apology,

303
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:54,390
- just pay us.
- She's right.

304
00:20:54,690 --> 00:20:57,060
If compensation is needed,
I'll provide it.

305
00:20:57,690 --> 00:21:01,330
However, I'll only be responsible
if my appraisal is proven incorrect.

306
00:21:03,100 --> 00:21:07,100
Prove my appraisal was wrong,
then take legal action.

307
00:21:08,440 --> 00:21:10,140
If it's proven that I was at fault,

308
00:21:10,470 --> 00:21:11,710
I won't make excuses.

309
00:21:12,480 --> 00:21:14,310
I'll compensate you accordingly.

310
00:21:14,610 --> 00:21:17,110
- How will you compensate us?
- Are you kidding me?

311
00:21:17,110 --> 00:21:19,950
- Please, stop this!
- I demand answers!

312
00:21:20,020 --> 00:21:21,620
Just fix this mess first!

313
00:21:21,690 --> 00:21:24,250
Hold on.
Why don't we take this outside?

314
00:21:24,420 --> 00:21:27,090
We'll take this outside
and talk it through.

315
00:21:27,490 --> 00:21:29,290
- Move!
- I'm not budging.

316
00:21:33,660 --> 00:21:37,070
I trusted this certificate
and bought a gift for my parents!

317
00:21:37,870 --> 00:21:38,870
How could you...

318
00:21:38,870 --> 00:21:41,910
President Kim isn't fazed at all.

319
00:21:43,470 --> 00:21:47,140
You'd think her reputation and pride
would be completely shattered.

320
00:21:49,050 --> 00:21:51,010
That's because
it wasn't an honest mistake.

321
00:21:55,850 --> 00:21:58,690
I think the chairman put her up
to something shady again.

322
00:21:59,960 --> 00:22:01,730
That competition
my father was talking about.

323
00:22:02,430 --> 00:22:04,190
If it's something shady,
don't even get involved.

324
00:22:04,730 --> 00:22:06,130
You don't have to worry.

325
00:22:07,130 --> 00:22:10,170
I'm just as capable...

326
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:12,740
as President Kim.

327
00:22:17,610 --> 00:22:21,410
Who are you looking at right now
and what are you thinking?

328
00:22:21,910 --> 00:22:22,910
I can't...

329
00:22:23,550 --> 00:22:25,450
even ask you that, can I?

330
00:22:31,690 --> 00:22:34,790
She has Hyun Jun under her spell.

331
00:22:35,830 --> 00:22:39,030
How do I pry him away
from that what's-her-name?

332
00:22:39,660 --> 00:22:41,200
I happen to think Chloe...

333
00:22:42,630 --> 00:22:43,730
is a perfectly nice person.

334
00:22:44,770 --> 00:22:46,770
What's so nice about her?

335
00:22:46,870 --> 00:22:49,940
But "our" Hyun Jun loves her.

336
00:22:50,140 --> 00:22:51,780
Love? What a joke.

337
00:22:52,480 --> 00:22:54,410
What do you even know about love?

338
00:22:55,550 --> 00:22:56,810
When a man...

339
00:22:57,350 --> 00:23:01,820
loves a woman so much
that he decides to marry her?

340
00:23:02,220 --> 00:23:03,220
That feeling?

341
00:23:04,420 --> 00:23:06,960
It means he's giving her
his entire life.

342
00:23:07,290 --> 00:23:11,660
Why should I let my son
waste his life on that thing?

343
00:23:15,630 --> 00:23:18,170
Also, why do you keep
calling him "our" Hyun Jun?

344
00:23:18,170 --> 00:23:21,040
What gives you the right
to call him that?

345
00:23:26,740 --> 00:23:29,110
Director Seo, my head is killing me
as it is, so...

346
00:23:31,080 --> 00:23:32,080
What was that?

347
00:23:32,550 --> 00:23:33,920
Kim Myung Hui is in trouble?

348
00:23:37,050 --> 00:23:40,420
Is that so? So that's what happened.

349
00:23:49,330 --> 00:23:52,770
Then you should've called me.

350
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:55,340
How could you just let them
gang up on her like that?

351
00:23:56,340 --> 00:23:58,240
You're not hurt, are you?

352
00:23:59,580 --> 00:24:03,750
How could you have helped?
Besides, I'd never let her get hurt.

353
00:24:04,210 --> 00:24:05,620
She may be physically fine,

354
00:24:06,580 --> 00:24:08,150
but she might be hurting inside.

355
00:24:09,550 --> 00:24:10,650
You have a point.

356
00:24:11,720 --> 00:24:14,960
People used to line up
just to get an appraisal from you.

357
00:24:15,630 --> 00:24:16,960
To think that overnight...

358
00:24:18,760 --> 00:24:19,930
You must be upset.

359
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:26,740
What's on your mind?

360
00:24:28,210 --> 00:24:29,340
Kill two birds with one stone.

361
00:24:30,740 --> 00:24:32,980
I'll use Assemblyman Kwon
to protect myself,

362
00:24:33,380 --> 00:24:35,080
and get to the bottom
of the trade deal.

363
00:24:44,890 --> 00:24:47,360
For crying out loud.

364
00:24:47,760 --> 00:24:50,360
I can't believe
that greedy Assemblyman Kwon...

365
00:24:50,360 --> 00:24:52,330
gave the money back.

366
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,200
Darn it!

367
00:24:55,130 --> 00:24:57,570
I have to find a way
to change his mind.

368
00:25:02,270 --> 00:25:04,670
What now?

369
00:25:05,580 --> 00:25:08,080
Fire Kim Myung Hui.

370
00:25:08,210 --> 00:25:10,050
Give me a break, will you?

371
00:25:11,050 --> 00:25:14,280
I've already got enough on my plate
with Assemblyman Kwon.

372
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:16,750
And now you're trying
to stir up more trouble?

373
00:25:16,820 --> 00:25:20,220
Thanks to Hyun Jun, my head's
about to explode just like yours.

374
00:25:21,120 --> 00:25:24,160
Still, we have to do
what's right for Adele.

375
00:25:24,390 --> 00:25:27,430
I heard there are still protests,
and it's a total mess.

376
00:25:27,800 --> 00:25:30,870
It'll just be one mess after another
with Kim Myung Hui in charge.

377
00:25:36,910 --> 00:25:39,480
Sir, you're going
to want to see this.

378
00:25:47,380 --> 00:25:48,690
Assemblyman Kwon.

379
00:25:49,450 --> 00:25:50,850
What brings you here?

380
00:25:51,860 --> 00:25:54,690
As you can see,
I'm here to see President Kim.

381
00:25:55,760 --> 00:25:57,390
President Kim told me...

382
00:25:58,090 --> 00:26:00,900
to file a complaint
about the appraisal mistake.

383
00:26:01,700 --> 00:26:04,830
She said I must be seen protesting
just like everyone else.

384
00:26:05,370 --> 00:26:09,040
That way, I'll look like a victim
and not a party to the deal.

385
00:26:10,270 --> 00:26:13,010
She had a point, so I stopped by.

386
00:26:14,040 --> 00:26:16,150
I see.

387
00:26:18,950 --> 00:26:20,720
After hearing President Kim out,

388
00:26:21,120 --> 00:26:23,650
I think I may have been a bit hasty.

389
00:26:24,520 --> 00:26:27,560
This whole thing would've been fine
once the suspicions died down.

390
00:26:28,630 --> 00:26:30,960
Do you really think so?

391
00:26:38,600 --> 00:26:40,270
All right, then.

392
00:26:40,270 --> 00:26:43,140
Let's go to my office
and discuss this further.

393
00:26:45,110 --> 00:26:46,110
Manager Kang.

394
00:26:51,310 --> 00:26:52,320
Right this way, sir.

395
00:26:54,820 --> 00:26:55,890
Take good care of him.

396
00:27:03,960 --> 00:27:05,160
How did you persuade him?

397
00:27:05,300 --> 00:27:08,830
I arranged the meeting
to help Assemblyman Kwon save face,

398
00:27:09,170 --> 00:27:11,430
but he showed his greedy side first.

399
00:27:12,470 --> 00:27:15,410
It seems he wants double
the original lobbying funds.

400
00:27:16,070 --> 00:27:18,070
What? Double?

401
00:27:21,440 --> 00:27:22,480
That greedy little...

402
00:27:29,450 --> 00:27:32,590
You already swayed Assemblyman Kwon
to be your shield?

403
00:27:32,960 --> 00:27:35,730
It was obvious you'd use
the protesters as an excuse...

404
00:27:36,230 --> 00:27:38,560
to push me out as president.

405
00:27:39,060 --> 00:27:40,130
I had to be prepared.

406
00:27:41,630 --> 00:27:43,870
Always so sly.

407
00:27:48,640 --> 00:27:49,670
You're not the only one...

408
00:27:50,240 --> 00:27:53,310
who can use the protesters
to your advantage.

409
00:27:54,540 --> 00:27:57,510
I can use them too,

410
00:27:57,880 --> 00:27:59,820
along with Assemblyman Kwon.

411
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:04,390
I'll protect my position myself,

412
00:28:04,950 --> 00:28:06,360
so don't waste your energy
on obvious ploys.

413
00:28:08,020 --> 00:28:10,930
Fine.
Let's see how well you protect it.

414
00:28:11,590 --> 00:28:14,760
Try as hard as you want,
but it can be taken in an instant.

415
00:28:22,370 --> 00:28:23,370
She's right.

416
00:28:24,770 --> 00:28:27,710
It can all be taken away
in an instant.

417
00:28:35,790 --> 00:28:37,750
Double the lobbying funds?

418
00:28:38,460 --> 00:28:40,190
Double, as in 40 million dollars?

419
00:28:54,270 --> 00:28:56,340
(BIT Life, President Kim Myung Hui)

420
00:28:56,710 --> 00:28:59,210
So you stopped Oh Jung Ran
thanks to Assemblyman Kwon,

421
00:28:59,410 --> 00:29:01,080
figured out
what kind of person he is,

422
00:29:01,380 --> 00:29:03,710
and confirmed what would happen
with the development deal.

423
00:29:04,810 --> 00:29:08,120
Assemblyman Kwon values greed
more than his reputation.

424
00:29:08,550 --> 00:29:11,620
He didn't care
when I offered to quash the rumors,

425
00:29:12,690 --> 00:29:13,960
but the moment I hinted...

426
00:29:13,960 --> 00:29:16,660
that Chairman Park might double
the lobbying funds,

427
00:29:17,090 --> 00:29:19,460
he came running, didn't he?

428
00:29:20,700 --> 00:29:23,300
If their interests align,

429
00:29:23,630 --> 00:29:25,270
those two will make a deal again
in a heartbeat.

430
00:29:25,940 --> 00:29:28,200
So, what's the next step?

431
00:29:28,640 --> 00:29:31,370
It'll be hard to interfere
every time they make a deal.

432
00:29:33,580 --> 00:29:36,610
What if I use it to my advantage
instead of interfering?

433
00:29:36,910 --> 00:29:38,380
Use the deal to your advantage?

434
00:29:38,980 --> 00:29:41,420
Chairman Park won't give up
on this deal.

435
00:29:42,120 --> 00:29:44,320
If the lobbying funds keep growing,

436
00:29:44,890 --> 00:29:48,120
he'll have to dip
into his slush fund.

437
00:29:49,260 --> 00:29:53,200
Then you'll finally find out
where he keeps his money.

438
00:29:53,660 --> 00:29:56,930
You'll get a chance to find
the slush fund ledgers or evidence.

439
00:29:57,530 --> 00:29:58,540
Exactly.

440
00:29:59,140 --> 00:30:01,400
This deal can't fall through
completely.

441
00:30:02,340 --> 00:30:03,970
I'm going to keep
raising the stakes...

442
00:30:04,510 --> 00:30:07,540
and use it as a trap
to catch Park Tae Ho.

443
00:30:11,750 --> 00:30:14,180
Assemblyman Kwon, please forgive
the humble accommodations.

444
00:30:15,250 --> 00:30:16,250
After you.

445
00:30:30,770 --> 00:30:34,370
Yes. We can put a complete stop
to Chairman Park's deal.

446
00:30:35,510 --> 00:30:37,110
Now that I have photo evidence,

447
00:30:37,410 --> 00:30:40,140
release the article we prepared
immediately.

448
00:30:41,910 --> 00:30:43,580
What article are you referring to?

449
00:30:46,680 --> 00:30:47,720
(Chairman's Office)

450
00:31:29,830 --> 00:31:32,700
(Pearl in Red)

451
00:31:32,800 --> 00:31:35,600
Persuade Assemblyman Kwon
to come back.

452
00:31:35,730 --> 00:31:38,770
Tell him
I'll triple the lobbying funds.

453
00:31:38,900 --> 00:31:43,110
Since you've made your decision,
I'll do my best to help, sir.

454
00:31:43,210 --> 00:31:46,240
Even with my mother's objections,
I can't give up on this marriage,

455
00:31:46,440 --> 00:31:48,040
so I have to win the competition.

456
00:31:48,310 --> 00:31:50,910
You'll take my side
and help me, right?

457
00:31:51,480 --> 00:31:52,550
By your side, Hyun Jun?

458
00:31:52,680 --> 00:31:55,150
Can you beat that Chloe girl?

459
00:31:55,250 --> 00:31:57,320
It doesn't matter if you can or not.

460
00:31:57,320 --> 00:31:59,460
You have to win
and marry Park Min Jun.

461
00:32:00,590 --> 00:32:02,590
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
